# 7-Day Nextjs Web Design

Use this rule when a project should follow a seven-day Next.js-aware design sprint.

## Day Targets

- Day 1: brief, users, constraints, runtime assumptions
- Day 2: route tree, app router segments, layout hierarchy
- Day 3: server versus client boundaries and data architecture
- Day 4: route-mapped wireframes and key states
- Day 5: visual system and component inventory
- Day 6: accessibility, metadata, auth, and performance review
- Day 7: Next.js-focused implementation handoff

## Rules

- keep route and layout structure explicit
- make server versus client decisions visible
- include metadata and SEO requirements
- include auth, loading, and error-state considerations
